# build outputs
dist/
src-tauri/target/

# machine-written files — their generators own the formatting
pnpm-lock.yaml
src/domain/generated/
src-tauri/gen/

# fleet-distributed files — akira-toriyama/.github owns them and the fleet-sync
# workflow overwrites them wholesale, so a local reformat is reverted on its
# next run (and lands on main unchecked: ci.yml runs on pull_request only).
# Everything here is fleet's except ci.yml, which is vista's own and stays
# formatted. Listing the directory itself (.github/**) would exclude the parent
# and make the ci.yml negation unreachable — hence the per-file globs.
.github/*.yml
.github/workflows/*
!.github/workflows/ci.yml
docs/commit-convention.md
